==English==

===Etymology===
Aphetic for obsolete ''[[evanish]]'', Old French ''[[esvanir]], [[esvaniss-]]'' (French ''[[évanouir]]''), Vulgar Latin ''[[evanescere]]'', from ''[[vanus]]'', "empty".

===Pronunciation===
*{{AHD|văn'ĭsh}}
*{{IPA|/ˈvænɪʃ/}}
*{{SAMPA|/"v@nIS/}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|vanish|es}}

# To become [[invisible]] or move out of [[view]] [[unnoticed]].
#{{Mathematics}} To become [[equal]] to [[zero]].
#:''The function f(x)=x^2 '''vanishes''' at x=0.''

====Synonyms====
*[[disappear]]

